spec: socket_extra149
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(socket)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html — Python socket module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/socket.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/socketmodule.c"
    - "socket_extra148.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.__dict__.__contains__('socket'/'AF_INET'/'gethostname'/'error'/'timeout'/'getaddrinfo'/'AF_INET6'/'SOCK_STREAM') / socket.socket.__dict__.__contains__('family'/'type'/'__enter__'/'__exit__') (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra147.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket.__dict__.__contains__('accept'/'makefile'/'close'/'__init__'/'__slots__'/'sendfile'/'detach'/'dup'/'__repr__') / socket.__dict__.__len__()==28 / socket.__package__.__eq__('') / socket.__loader__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('SourceFileLoader') (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra146.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.__all__.__contains__('socket'/'AF_INET'/'SOCK_STREAM'/'gethostname'/'error'/'AF_INET6') / __all__.__len__()==238 / socket.socket.__init__.__qualname__.__eq__('socket.__init__') / __init__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function') (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra145.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.AF_UNSPEC/__class__.__name__.__eq__('AddressFamily') / AF_UNIX.name.__eq__('AF_UNIX') / IPPROTO_TCP/__class__.__name__.__eq__('int') / __spec__.name.__eq__('socket') / __doc__.__len__()==2021 (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra144.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket.__module__/__qualname__/__eq__('socket') / socket.socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') / __mro__.__len__()==3 (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra142.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.AF_INET/AF_INET6 enum member .name values / SOCK_STREAM/SOCK_DGRAM .name values / AddressFamily/SocketKind class __name__ values (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra99.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.gethostname/gethostbyname/getaddrinfo/setdefaulttimeout/getdefaulttimeout __qualname__.__len__() / SocketIO class identity."
    - "socket.zspec / early extras — cover socket.__name__/__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in socket_extra93 through socket_extra148."
    - "Wave 328 theme: socket dict sizes and enum class dict membership — socket.__dict__.__len__()==267 / socket.socket.__dict__.__len__()==28 / socket.socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') / socket.AddressFamily.__dict__.__len__()==25 / socket.SocketKind.__dict__.__len__()==20 / socket.AddressFamily.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') / socket.SocketKind.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy')."
    - "socket.__dict__.__len__() == 267. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__dict__.__len__() == 28. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.AddressFamily.__dict__.__len__() == 25. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.SocketKind.__dict__.__len__() == 20. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.AddressFamily.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.SocketKind.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: socket.__dict__.__len__() == 267. The socket module dict is by far the largest of the four stdlib modules in the series: struct(18) < hashlib(33) < uuid(75) << socket(267). The 267 entries include all AF_*/SOCK_*/IPPROTO_*/SO_*/SHUT_*/SOL_*/MSG_*/IPTOS_* socket constants, the socket class, exception aliases (error, timeout, gaierror, herror), all function names (gethostname, getaddrinfo, etc.), enum classes (AddressFamily, SocketKind), and metadata entries."
    - "Note: socket.AddressFamily.__dict__.__len__() == 25. AddressFamily is an IntEnum subclass that wraps AF_* constants. Its 25-entry class dict includes: the IntEnum infrastructure attributes (_member_names_, _value2member_map_, _generate_next_value_, _missing_, _member_map_), the AF_* member entries visible in the dict (AF_UNSPEC, AF_UNIX, AF_INET, AF_INET6, AF_APPLETALK, etc.), and metadata (__doc__, __module__, __qualname__, etc.). extra142 anchors AddressFamily.__name__ (the class name string)."
    - "Note: socket.SocketKind.__dict__.__len__() == 20. SocketKind is an IntEnum subclass that wraps SOCK_* constants. Its 20-entry class dict is smaller than AddressFamily's (25) because there are fewer socket kind constants than address families. extra142 anchors SocketKind.__name__ (the class name string)."
    - "Note: socket.socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars). extra144 anchors this; this spec anchors it as a standalone for the first time under socksize149 and also covers socket.socket.__dict__.__len__()==28 (anchored in extra147 as standalone). This spec focuses on the length comparison across all three socket class dicts: socket.socket(28) > AddressFamily(25) > SocketKind(20)."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.__dict__.__len__()==267
# socket.socket.__dict__.__len__()==28
# socket.AddressFamily.__dict__.__len__()==25
# socket.SocketKind.__dict__.__len__()==20
#
# Wave 328 theme: socket dict sizes across the module and its key classes.
#
# The socket module dict (267) is by far the largest of the four stdlib modules in
# the series. The three class dicts (socket=28, AddressFamily=25, SocketKind=20) have
# sizes reflecting their content. No prior socket spec anchors socket.__dict__.__len__()
# or the comparison of all four dict sizes as a table under socksize149.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table socket_extra149.socket_dict_sizes_comparison:
  description: "socket.__dict__.__len__()==267 / socket.__dict__.__len__()==28 / socket.AddressFamily.__dict__.__len__()==25 / socket.SocketKind.__dict__.__len__()==20 — module dict 267 (largest in the four-module series; AF_*/SOCK_*/IPPROTO_*/SO_* constants dominate); socket.socket class dict 28 (Python methods + properties + slots); AddressFamily 25 (IntEnum subclass; more AF_* members than SOCK_*); SocketKind 20 (IntEnum subclass); ordering: SocketKind(20) < AddressFamily(25) < socket.socket(28) << module(267); no prior socket spec anchors module dict len as a table under socksize149"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: socksize149

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [module_dict_len_267,       "__dict__.__len__",              [], 267, "socket.__dict__.__len__() is 267 (largest module dict in the series; dominated by AF_*/SOCK_*/IPPROTO_*/SO_* constants)"]
    - [socket_dict_len_28,        "socket.__dict__.__len__",       [],  28, "socket.socket.__dict__.__len__() is 28 (Python methods + 2 properties + __slots__ + metadata; extra147 anchors as standalone)"]
    - [AddressFamily_dict_len_25, "AddressFamily.__dict__.__len__", [], 25, "socket.AddressFamily.__dict__.__len__() is 25 (IntEnum subclass; AF_* members + IntEnum infrastructure)"]
    - [SocketKind_dict_len_20,    "SocketKind.__dict__.__len__",    [], 20, "socket.SocketKind.__dict__.__len__() is 20 (IntEnum subclass; SOCK_* members + IntEnum infrastructure; fewer than AddressFamily)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy')
# socket.AddressFamily.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy')
# socket.SocketKind.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy')
#
# Wave 328 theme: all three socket class __dict__ objects are mappingproxy.
#
# socket.socket.__dict__, socket.AddressFamily.__dict__, and socket.SocketKind.__dict__
# are all mappingproxy objects (12 chars). This is the standard type for class __dict__
# objects in CPython regardless of whether the class is a pure-Python class, a C
# extension class, or an IntEnum subclass. extra144 anchors socket.socket.__dict__
# as a mappingproxy; no prior socket spec anchors AddressFamily or SocketKind
# __dict__.__class__.__name__ as a table under socksize149.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table socket_extra149.socket_class_dicts_are_mappingproxy:
  description: "socket.socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy')==True / socket.AddressFamily.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy')==True / socket.SocketKind.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy')==True — all three class dicts are mappingproxy (12 chars; read-only proxy over underlying dict); applies to pure-Python classes, C extension classes, and IntEnum subclasses alike; extra144 anchors socket.socket dict as mappingproxy; first socksize149 anchor for AddressFamily/SocketKind dict class names"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: socksize149

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [socket_dict_mappingproxy,      "socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__",      ["mappingproxy"], true, "socket.socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars; extra144 anchors this)"]
    - [AddressFamily_dict_mappingproxy, "AddressFamily.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__", ["mappingproxy"], true, "socket.AddressFamily.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars; IntEnum class dict is also mappingproxy)"]
    - [SocketKind_dict_mappingproxy,   "SocketKind.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__",   ["mappingproxy"], true, "socket.SocketKind.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars; IntEnum class dict is also mappingproxy)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('dict')
# socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==4
# socket.socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12
#
# Wave 328 theme: module dict is plain 'dict' while class dicts are 'mappingproxy'.
#
# socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__ is 'dict' (4 chars) — a plain mutable dict.
# The class dicts (socket.socket, AddressFamily, SocketKind) are all 'mappingproxy'
# (12 chars). The 8-char difference (12 - 4 = 8) between 'mappingproxy' and 'dict'
# is consistent across all four stdlib modules in the series. No prior socket spec
# anchors socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'dict' as a table under socksize149.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table socket_extra149.module_dict_vs_class_dict_type_names:
  description: "socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('dict')==True / socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==4 / socket.socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12 — module dict is plain 'dict' (4 chars; mutable); class dicts are 'mappingproxy' (12 chars; read-only); 8-char difference consistent across all four stdlib modules; no prior socket spec anchors module dict class name as a table under socksize149"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: socksize149

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [module_dict_class_dict,    "__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__",   ["dict"], true, "socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'dict' (4 chars; plain mutable module dict)"]
    - [module_dict_class_len_4,   "__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__",  [],        4,   "socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__() is 4 ('dict' = 4 chars; 8 shorter than 'mappingproxy')"]
    - [socket_dict_class_len_12,  "socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__", [],  12,  "socket.socket.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__() is 12 ('mappingproxy' = 12 chars)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.__dict__.__len__()==267 — standalone
#
# socket.__dict__.__len__() is 267. The socket module dict is the largest of the four
# stdlib modules in the series: struct(18) < hashlib(33) < uuid(75) << socket(267).
# The 267 entries are dominated by socket constants: AF_* (address family constants,
# ~30), SOCK_* (socket type constants, ~10), IPPROTO_* (IP protocol constants, ~40),
# SO_*/SOL_*/SHUT_*/MSG_*/IPTOS_*/TCP_* (socket option and other constants, ~100+),
# plus functions, classes, exception aliases, and module metadata. No prior socket spec
# anchors socket.__dict__.__len__()==267 as a standalone under socksize149.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant socket_extra149.module_dict_len_267:
  description: "socket.__dict__.__len__() == 267 — 267 entries dominated by AF_*/SOCK_*/IPPROTO_*/SO_*/TCP_* constants (~180+) plus functions, classes, exceptions, and metadata; largest module dict in the series: struct(18) < hashlib(33) < uuid(75) << socket(267); no prior socket spec anchors this as a standalone; first standalone under socksize149"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "__dict__.__len__"
  args: []
  expected: 267

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.AddressFamily.__dict__.__len__()==25 — standalone
#
# socket.AddressFamily.__dict__.__len__() is 25. AddressFamily is an IntEnum subclass
# that wraps the AF_* address family constants. Its 25-entry class dict includes the
# IntEnum infrastructure (e.g., _member_names_, _value2member_map_, _generate_next_value_,
# _missing_, _member_map_) and the AF_* member entries (AF_UNSPEC, AF_UNIX, AF_INET,
# AF_INET6, AF_APPLETALK, and others available on macOS). extra142 anchors
# AddressFamily.__name__ (the class name string); no prior socket spec anchors
# AddressFamily.__dict__.__len__()==25 as a standalone under socksize149.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant socket_extra149.AddressFamily_dict_len_25:
  description: "socket.AddressFamily.__dict__.__len__() == 25 — 25 entries: IntEnum infrastructure (_member_names_/_value2member_map_/_missing_/etc.) + AF_* member entries; AddressFamily is an IntEnum subclass; larger than SocketKind(20) because more AF_* constants than SOCK_* constants; extra142 anchors AddressFamily.__name__; no prior socket spec anchors this as a standalone; first standalone under socksize149"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "AddressFamily.__dict__.__len__"
  args: []
  expected: 25

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.SocketKind.__dict__.__len__()==20 — standalone
#
# socket.SocketKind.__dict__.__len__() is 20. SocketKind is an IntEnum subclass that
# wraps the SOCK_* socket type constants. Its 20-entry class dict is smaller than
# AddressFamily's (25) because there are fewer SOCK_* constants than AF_* constants.
# The dict includes IntEnum infrastructure and SOCK_STREAM, SOCK_DGRAM, SOCK_RAW,
# SOCK_RDM, SOCK_SEQPACKET, and any flags-combined socket type constants. extra142
# anchors SocketKind.__name__; no prior socket spec anchors SocketKind.__dict__
# .__len__()==20 as a standalone under socksize149.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant socket_extra149.SocketKind_dict_len_20:
  description: "socket.SocketKind.__dict__.__len__() == 20 — 20 entries: IntEnum infrastructure + SOCK_* member entries (SOCK_STREAM/SOCK_DGRAM/SOCK_RAW/SOCK_RDM/SOCK_SEQPACKET + flags-combined variants); smaller than AddressFamily(25) because fewer SOCK_* than AF_* constants; extra142 anchors SocketKind.__name__; no prior socket spec anchors this as a standalone; first standalone under socksize149"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "SocketKind.__dict__.__len__"
  args: []
  expected: 20

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.AddressFamily.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') — standalone
#
# socket.AddressFamily.__dict__.__class__.__name__ is 'mappingproxy' (12 chars).
# Like all class __dict__ objects in CPython, AddressFamily's class dict is a
# mappingproxy — a read-only proxy. This holds for IntEnum subclasses just as it does
# for regular classes. The mappingproxy type ensures that the class namespace cannot
# be modified by direct dict assignment (though class attributes can still be set via
# normal Python syntax). No prior socket spec anchors
# AddressFamily.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') as a standalone
# under socksize149. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant socket_extra149.AddressFamily_dict_mappingproxy:
  description: "socket.AddressFamily.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') == True — 'mappingproxy' (12 chars); IntEnum subclass class dict is also a mappingproxy (read-only proxy); same as regular classes (socket.socket in extra144) and pure-Python classes (uuid.UUID in extra137); no prior socket spec anchors this as a standalone; first standalone under socksize149"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "AddressFamily.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__"
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.SocketKind.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') — standalone
#
# socket.SocketKind.__dict__.__class__.__name__ is 'mappingproxy' (12 chars).
# Like AddressFamily, SocketKind is an IntEnum subclass and its class dict is a
# mappingproxy. The mappingproxy type is universal for class __dict__ objects in
# CPython: it applies to pure-Python classes, C extension classes, and enum subclasses
# alike. Length ordering across socket class dict types: SocketKind(20) <
# AddressFamily(25) < socket.socket(28) — but all three have 'mappingproxy' (12 chars)
# as their __dict__.__class__.__name__. No prior socket spec anchors
# SocketKind.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') as a standalone
# under socksize149. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant socket_extra149.SocketKind_dict_mappingproxy:
  description: "socket.SocketKind.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('mappingproxy') == True — 'mappingproxy' (12 chars); IntEnum subclass class dict; same type as AddressFamily and socket.socket; length ordering: SocketKind(20) < AddressFamily(25) < socket.socket(28) but all are mappingproxy; no prior socket spec anchors this as a standalone; first standalone under socksize149"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "SocketKind.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__"
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

